      "message": "In some distant future the standard library may eventually get real hash tables like flat_map and flat_set (and hopefully stop using generic sounding names for specific implementations). In any event, unordered_set is kinda bad, especially for this sort of constant pushing and popping. Can we use SkTHashSet here?\n\nThere are examples of how to use it and create the required hash function for SkTHashSet at tests/HashTest.cpp, in particular the part with CopyCounter. A more real example might be OneLineShaper::FontKey::Hasher::operator() in OneLineShaper.cpp.",
