      "side": 1,
      "message": "\u003e In some distant future the standard library may eventually get real hash tables like flat_map and flat_set (and hopefully stop using generic sounding names for specific implementations). In any event, unordered_set is kinda bad, especially for this sort of constant pushing and popping. Can we use SkTHashSet here?\n\nInteresting - can you elaborate - what\u0027s bad about unordered_set and how does its implementation differ from SkTHashSet?\n\nSwitched to SkTHashSet as suggested and added simple hash and operator\u003d().",
      "parentUuid": "b559131d_ca7c6a4e",
      "revId": "ba4952ae3745c6edfeca420bcf1e30716772481f",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02"
